e English-speaking world, where its use has been reinforced by the fact that the name was adopted in the 19th century for a garden flower, a large cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Marguerite Turnbull of Minto was born in 1332, in Galston, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, her father, Sir John Turnbull, was 17 and her mother, Lady Mary Haliburton, was 15. She married Sir Alexander Stewart 5th Laird of Darnley before 1366, in Lanarkshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1381, in Darnley, Renfrewshire, Scotland, at the age of 49, and was buried in Dunkeld, Perthshire, Scotland."},"et":{"1332–1381":"1332–1381","1345–1423":"1345–1423","1347–1381":"1347–1381","1342–1404":"1342–1404","1366–1402":"1366–1402","1315–1355":"1315–1355","1317–1347":"1317–1347","before 1366":"enne 1366","1340":"1340","1381":"1381","1404":"1404","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","1402":"1402","1423":"1423","1345":"1345","1355":"1355","1366":"1366","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","1317":"1317","Dunkeld, Perthshire, Scotland":"Dunkeld, Perthshire, Scotland","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","Darnley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Darnley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Galston, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Galston, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland",", , , Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Battle of Nesbitt Moor, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1332–1381":"1332–1381","1345–1423":"1345–1423","1347–1381":"1347–1381","1342–1404":"1342–1404","1366–1402":"1366–1402","1315–1355":"1315–1355","1317–1347":"1317–1347","before 1366":"ennen vuotta 1366","1340":"1340","1381":"1381","1404":"1404","1315":"1315","1347":"1347",